{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2016}}
'''Georgie Badiel Liberty''' (born February 7, 1985) is a [[List of Burkinabés|Burkinabé]] model and activist living and working in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbadiel/georgiebadiel/|title=Georgie Badiel - Fashion Model - Profile on New York Magazine|publisher=nymag.com|accessdate=July 17, 2016}}</ref> Badiel was Miss Burkina Faso in 2003 and Miss Africa 2004.
She is also an author and activist who has taken on the issue of the lack of [[potable]] drinking water in her West African homeland. Therein she runs the [[Georgie Badiel Foundation]] which is dedicated to raising funds to support the cause.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://georgiebadielfoundation.org|title=Georgie Badiel Foundation - Activist|date=July 23, 2015|publisher=georgiebadielfoundation.org|accessdate=July 17, 2016}}</ref> Now together with the children's book author, [[Peter H. Reynolds]] and Susan Verde, she has co-created the book ''The Water Princess'', a picture book which tells the story of her West African nation's desperate need for aquifers through her life as a young girl who dreams of bringing clean water to her people. The book was published by [[Penguin Random House]] in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/childrens/childrens-book-news/article/61048-the-water-princess-relates-childhood-of-burkina-faso-born-model-georgie-badiel.html|title='The Water Princess' Relates Childhood of Burkina Faso-Born Model Georgie Badiel|publisher=publishersweekly.com|accessdate=July 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/317197/the-water-princess-by-susan-verde-with-georgie-badiel-illustrated-by-peter-h-reynolds/9780399172588|title=The Water Princess by Susan Verde, Georgie Badiel - PenguinRandomHouse.com|publisher=|accessdate=August 23, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/13/books/review/how-do-you-explain-the-refugee-crisis-to-children-new-picture-books-can-help.html | title=How Do You Explain the Refugee Crisis to Children? New Picture Books Can Help|first=Deborah | last=Ellis | date=November 11, 2016 | accessdate=December 11, 2016}}</ref>
Badiel is married to Chid Liberty and was honored Chevalier Of Merit Burkinabe on February 28 at the Burkina Faso mission in New York.
