{{Infobox football biography | name = Olivier Boscagli | image = | fullname = Olivier Maxime Boscagli<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fifadata.com/document/fwyc/2017/pdf/fwyc_2017_squadlists.pdf|title=FIFA U-20 World Cup Korea Republic 2017: List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF|date=9 January 2017 |access-date=2 March 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|11|18|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Monaco]]<ref>[http://www.ogcnice.com/fr/equipes/cfa/effectif/joueur/351/boscagli Olivier Boscagli's profile on OGC Nice website]</ref> | height = 1.81m | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[OGC Nice|Nice]] | clubnumber = 28 | youthyears1 = 2003–2011 | youthclubs1 = FC Beausoleil | youthyears2 = 2011 | youthclubs2 = [[OGC Nice|Nice]] | youthyears3 = 2011–2013 | youthclubs3 = FC Beausoleil | youthyears4 = 2013–2015 | youthclubs4 = [[OGC Nice|Nice]] | years1 = 2014–2017 | clubs1 = [[OGC Nice|Nice II]] | caps1 = 44 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2015– | clubs2 = [[OGC Nice|Nice]] | caps2 = 16 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2017–2018 | clubs3 = → [[Nîmes Olympique|Nîmes]] (loan) | caps3 = 28 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2014 | nationalteam1 = [[France national under-17 football team|France U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2015 | nationalteam2 = [[France national under-18 football team|France U18]] | nationalcaps2 = 5 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2015–2016 | nationalteam3 = [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]] | nationalcaps3 = 16 | nationalgoals3 = 1 | nationalyears4 = 2016–2017 | nationalteam4 = [[France national under-20 football team|France U20]] | nationalcaps4 = 10 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | nationalyears5 = 2017– | nationalteam5 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] | nationalcaps5 = 5 | nationalgoals5 = 0 | club-update = 21:25, 18 August 2018 (UTC) | ntupdate = 7 September 2018 }}
'''Olivier Maxime Boscagli''' (18 November 1997) is a French [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[OGC Nice]].<ref name="soccerway">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/olivier-boscagli/329542/|title=France - O. Boscagli - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> He represented France's youth teams from [[France national under-17 football team|U17]] until [[France national under-20 football team|U20]].
==Club career== Boscagli is a youth exponent from [[OGC Nice]]. He made his [[Ligue 1]] debut on 25 April 2015 against [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Stade Rennais]] playing the first 84 minutes in a 2–1 away defeat.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/04/25/france/ligue-1/stade-rennais-fc/olympique-gymnaste-club-de-nice-cote-dazur/1687373/|title=Rennes vs. Nice - 25 April 2015 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> He scored his first goal in Nice's 1–0 win over [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] on 18 December 2015, thereby becoming the youngest player to score in the Ligue 1 in the 2015–2016 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nice edge Montpellier thanks to teenager Boscagli's strike|url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/ligue-1/2015-2016/nice-edge-montpellier-thanks-to-teenager-boscagli-s-strike_sto5033397/story.shtml|accessdate=21 December 2015|work=Eurosport|date=18 December 2015}}</ref>
==International career== Although born on [[Monaco]], Boscagli represents France at international level due to the [[Monaco national football team]] not being a member of [[UEFA]] or [[FIFA]]. He played for France's [[France national under-17 football team|U17]], [[France national under-18 football team|U18]], [[France national under-19 football team|U19]], and [[France national under-20 football team|U20]] youth teams.<ref>{{cite web|title=Olivier Boscagli|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2543221931-olivier-boscagli|website=Fédération Française de Football|accessdate=6 June 2017|language=French}}</ref>
