{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{Infobox boxer| | name=Sapok Biki | image= | image_size= | caption = | realname = Sapok Biki | nickname = | nationality = Malaysian | weight = [[Light Flyweight]] | birth_date = 9 April 1974 | birth_place = [[Simunjan District|Simunjan]], [[Sarawak]], [[Malaysia]] | death_date = | death_place = | height = <!--| weight = 48 kg--> | medaltemplates= |style southpaw= |total = |wins 121= |KO =113 |losses = 7 |draws = 1 |no contests = 129 }} '''Sapok Biki''' (born 9 April 1974) is a [[Malaysia]]n [[Boxing|boxer]]. He won the gold medal in the [[light flyweight]] class at the [[1998 Commonwealth Games]] in [[Kuala Lumpur]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/Sport/Boxing/2014/07/30/Khirs-boxing-campaign-end-in-quarters/|title=Khir's boxing campaign ends in quarter-finals |date=30 July 2014|work=The Star|accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref> He also competed for his native country at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amateur-boxing.strefa.pl/Championships/OlympicGames1996.html|title=BOXING: 26.Olympic Games - Atlanta, USA - July 20 - August 4, 1996|publisher=amateur-boxing.strefa.pl|accessdate=21 February 2015}}</ref> He has since retired from competition and become a coach.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nst.com.my/node/16422|title=BOXING: Sapok still in MABF’s mind |publisher=New Straits Times|accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref>
He is of [[Iban people|Iban]] descent from [[Simunjan District|Simunjan]], [[Sarawak]]. He is serving in the [[Malaysian Army]] as a [[Captain (land and air)|Captain]].
